            <div class="entity_block">
                <a class="avatar" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/ptolemean/">
                    <img src="http://blogs-images.forbes.com/cache/gravatars/ptolemean_40.jpg" alt="Ptolemean" />
                </a>



                <a class="user_name" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/ptolemean/">
                    Ptolemean
                </a>


   		<span class="timestamp">11 months ago</span>
    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		<p>The problem is and always has been the privatization of money. Period. The notion of creating common good through private interest is insidiously asinine. No matter what convoluted reasoning you offer the uninitiated, privatized control of money is precisely what makes it political – as in “render unto Caesar those things which are Caesars….”</p>

    	</div>



