            <div class="entity_block">
                <a class="avatar">
                    <img src='http://blogs-images.forbes.com/assets/images/avatars/generic_profile_image_62.jpg' alt="gs271" />
		</a>



                <a class="user_name nohover">
                    gs271
                </a>


   		<span class="timestamp">1 year ago</span>
    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		<p>This article really points out how much effect those indices have…. and that per se is excellent evidence of inefficient markets.</p> 
<p>a) everyone believes that the market is perfectly efficient because everyone supposedly knows everything</p> 
<p>b) the best deal you therefore get, such is the consensus, is to stick with the index</p> 
<p>but look at this paradox!! if nearly everyone believes in a) and b), then nearly no one does any ground research! Hence there is everything but perfect knowledge of assets and everything but perfectly efficient markets.<br /> Thank you.</p>

    	</div>



    	<div class="comment_controls" data-called-out-state="on">
			<div class="right_col">
				<a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/brendancoffey/2011/10/26/the-four-companies-that-control-the-147-companies-that-own-everything/?commentId=comment_blogAndPostId/blog/comment/1380-1458-535" class="permalink">Permalink</a>
